Relay new website "FFL Transfer" form submissions from the Valley Pawn site (https://thevalleypawn.com/ffl-transfer/) into Slack so the team can follow up quickly. Run quietly — only post when there is a genuinely new submission.

These submissions arrive as emails to jdavis@fcfpawn.com from the website's Jetpack contact form, with the subject "Website FFL Transfer Request". Use the Gmail MCP server mcp__00007879-ef17-43e5-9d59-6325cd2f0a31 and the Slack MCP server mcp__f92ce7c6-0353-4419-8491-f0843b182ff2.

STEP 1 — De-dup label. Ensure a Gmail label named "FFL-Web-Slacked" exists (list_labels; if missing, create_label). This label marks submissions already posted to Slack so they are never posted twice.

STEP 2 — Find new submissions. Search Gmail (search_threads) with query: subject:"Website FFL Transfer Request" newer_than:2d -label:FFL-Web-Slacked . Open each matching thread with get_thread to read the submission body.

STEP 3 — Post to Slack. For EACH new submission, post ONE message to channel #ffl-transfer-notifications (channel ID C0BA6SXL8AK) using slack_send_message. Parse the fields from the email body and format like:
:inbox_tray: *New FFL transfer request (website form)*
• Name: <value>
• Phone: <value>
• Email: <value or “—”>
• Pickup store: <value>
• Details: <value>
Received: <date/time from the email>
If a field is blank, show “—”. Keep it to that single tidy message per submission.

STEP 4 — Mark done. After successfully posting a submission to Slack, apply the "FFL-Web-Slacked" label to that message (label_message) so it is not posted again on the next run.

STEP 5 — Quiet when empty. If there are no new (unlabeled) submissions, do NOT post anything to Slack and do not send any other notification. Only the genuinely new ones get posted.

Notes: This is purely a notification relay — never reply to the customer, never send email, never delete anything. The store contacts for follow-up, if needed: Culpeper (540) 445-5510, Waynesboro (540) 221-6346, Harrisonburg (540) 574-4500, Lexington (540) 461-8349, Roanoke (540) 562-0776.